import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the overall unemployment rate distribution across all states?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('state')['rate'].mean()
    data_grouped = data_grouped.sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.bar(data_grouped.index, data_grouped.values)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('Which state has the highest unemployment rate?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    max_rate = data_grouped.max()
    max_state = data_grouped.idxmax()
    plt.axhline(max_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Rate: {max_state} ({max_rate:.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['id'], data['rate'], c=data['state'].astype(int), cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('State Population')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between state population and unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="States")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the mean unemployment rate for each state
    mean_rates = data.groupby('state')['rate'].mean()

    # Create a bar chart
    ax = mean_rates.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 6), color='blue', legend=True)

    # Set the title and labels
    plt.title('What is the average unemployment rate for each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Average Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    for state in data['state'].unique():
        state_data = data[data['state'] == state]
        plt.plot(state_data['date'], state_data['rate'], label=state)
    
    plt.title('How does the unemployment rate vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='State', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
